---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Axto // Yanis Amani"
  description="A marketplace for auto parts with a React Native mobile app and Astro admin portal."
>
  <section data-lang="en">
    <article class="project-page" data-animate>
      <div class="container">
        <h1 class="project-title">Axto</h1>
        <p class="project-tagline">A marketplace platform for auto parts. Mobile app for buyers, web dashboard for sellers, all backed by Supabase.</p>
        <div class="project-links">
          <span class="btn-primary" style="opacity: 0.5; cursor: default;">Private source</span>
        </div>

        <div class="project-tech-stack" data-animate>
          <span class="tech-label">Tech Stack</span>
          <div class="tech-list">
            <a href="https://reactnative.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="tech-tag">React Native</a>
            <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="tech-tag">Astro</a>
            <a href="https://supabase.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="tech-tag">Supabase</a>
            <a href="https://postgresql.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="tech-tag">Postgres</a>
            <a href="https://stripe.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="tech-tag">Stripe</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="project-content">
          <h2>What it does</h2>
          <p>Axto connects auto parts buyers and sellers. Buyers browse listings through a React Native app; sellers manage inventory, process orders, and track analytics through an Astro web dashboard. Vehicle compatibility matching ensures you only see parts that fit your car.</p>

          <h2>Architecture</h2>
          <p>Two frontends, one backend:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Mobile app</strong> — React Native (Expo). Browse by vehicle, search by part, save favourites, direct messaging with sellers. Push notifications for price drops and saved searches.</li>
            <li><strong>Admin dashboard</strong> — Astro with React islands. Inventory management, order fulfilment, sales analytics. Responsive — works on desktop and tablet.</li>
            <li><strong>Backend</strong> — Supabase handles auth, Postgres with Row Level Security, storage for part images, and real-time subscriptions for messaging.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Key decisions</h2>
          <p><strong>Vehicle compatibility as a graph problem.</strong> Instead of tagging every part with make/model/year (which is thousands of combinations), we modelled it as a compatibility matrix — each part has a set of "fits" rules, and the query engine walks the graph. More work upfront, but adding a new vehicle doesn't require retagging every part.</p>
          <p><strong>Supabase RLS for multi-tenant data.</strong> Every row in the database has a <code>seller_id</code>, and Row Level Security policies enforce that sellers only see their own orders and inventory. Buyers see only public listing data. This means the mobile app queries Postgres directly — no custom API layer needed for reads.</p>

          <h2>The hard parts</h2>
          <p><strong>Search.</strong> Postgres full-text search is fine for text, but auto parts have VIN-specific queries, OEM numbers, and fuzzy brand matching. We ended up with a hybrid: Postgres tsvector for full-text + a custom matching layer for compatibility queries.</p>
          <p><strong>Image moderation.</strong> Users upload part photos. We built an automated moderation pipeline using a third-party API, but the false-positive rate on engine parts vs. prohibited items was… educational.</p>

          <h2>Screenshots</h2>
          <div class="screenshot-grid">
            <figure class="screenshot">
              <img src="/axto-images/home.png" alt="Axto home screen" loading="lazy" width="200" height="433" />
              <figcaption>Home — Browse listings by vehicle</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="screenshot">
              <img src="/axto-images/search.png" alt="Axto search screen" loading="lazy" width="200" height="433" />
              <figcaption>Search — Find parts by name or OEM number</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="screenshot">
              <img src="/axto-images/product-details.png" alt="Axto product details" loading="lazy" width="200" height="433" />
              <figcaption>Product details — Compatibility info, price, seller</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="screenshot">
              <img src="/axto-images/cart-empty.png" alt="Empty cart" loading="lazy" width="200" height="433" />
              <figcaption>Cart — Empty state</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="screenshot">
              <img src="/axto-images/cart-with-products.png" alt="Cart with products" loading="lazy" width="200" height="433" />
              <figcaption>Cart — Items ready for checkout</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="screenshot">
              <img src="/axto-images/checkout-address.png" alt="Checkout address form" loading="lazy" width="200" height="433" />
              <figcaption>Checkout — Shipping address</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="screenshot">
              <img src="/axto-images/checkout-credit-card.png" alt="Checkout payment" loading="lazy" width="200" height="433" />
              <figcaption>Checkout — Payment via Stripe</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="screenshot">
              <img src="/axto-images/notifications.png" alt="Notifications" loading="lazy" width="200" height="433" />
              <figcaption>Notifications — Price drops and messages</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="screenshot">
              <img src="/axto-images/profile.png" alt="Profile screen" loading="lazy" width="200" height="433" />
              <figcaption>Profile — Account and saved searches</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>

          <h2>What I learned</h2>
          <p>This was my first full-stack marketplace and the project where I learned that <em>scope management is a skill, not a constraint</em>. The feature list kept growing — reviews, messaging, notifications, analytics — and each one taught me something about state management across platforms, real-time data sync, and why you don't skip writing integration tests for your Stripe webhook handler.</p>
          <p>Also: React Native's FlatList performance with 10,000+ parts listings is genuinely impressive. Astro's partial hydration meant the dashboard felt instant despite having React components embedded in static pages.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <nav class="project-nav">
      <div class="container project-nav-inner">
        <a href="/projects/mangaread" class="btn-ghost">← Previous project</a>
        <a href="/projects/yatsuscript" class="btn-ghost">Next project →</a>
      </div>
    </nav>
  </section>

  <section data-lang="fr">
    <article class="project-page" data-animate>
      <div class="container">
        <h1 class="project-title">Axto</h1>
        <p class="project-tagline">Une marketplace pour pièces auto. App mobile React Native pour les acheteurs, portail web Astro pour les vendeurs.</p>
        <div class="project-links">
          <span class="btn-primary" style="opacity: 0.5; cursor: default;">Source privée</span>
        </div>

        <div class="project-tech-stack" data-animate>
          <span class="tech-label">Stack Technique</span>
          <div class="tech-list">
            <a href="https://reactnative.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="tech-tag">React Native</a>
            <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="tech-tag">Astro</a>
            <a href="https://supabase.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="tech-tag">Supabase</a>
            <a href="https://postgresql.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="tech-tag">Postgres</a>
            <a href="https://stripe.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="tech-tag">Stripe</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="project-content">
          <h2>Ce que ça fait</h2>
          <p>Axto connecte acheteurs et vendeurs de pièces auto. Les acheteurs parcourent les annonces via une app React Native ; les vendeurs gèrent leur inventaire, les commandes et les analytics via un portail web Astro. La compatibilité véhicule assure que tu ne vois que les pièces qui correspondent à ta voiture.</p>

          <h2>Architecture</h2>
          <p>Deux frontends, un backend :</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>App mobile</strong> — React Native (Expo). Parcourir par véhicule, rechercher par pièce, favoris, messagerie directe. Notifications push pour les baisses de prix.</li>
            <li><strong>Dashboard admin</strong> — Astro avec îles React. Gestion d'inventaire, traitement des commandes, analytics des ventes. Responsive.</li>
            <li><strong>Backend</strong> — Supabase gère l'auth, Postgres avec Row Level Security, stockage d'images, souscriptions temps réel pour la messagerie.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Captures d'écran</h2>
          <div class="screenshot-grid">
            <figure class="screenshot">
              <img src="/axto-images/home.png" alt="Écran d'accueil Axto" loading="lazy" width="200" height="433" />
              <figcaption>Accueil — Parcourir les annonces par véhicule</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="screenshot">
              <img src="/axto-images/search.png" alt="Recherche Axto" loading="lazy" width="200" height="433" />
              <figcaption>Recherche — Trouver des pièces par nom ou numéro OEM</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="screenshot">
              <img src="/axto-images/product-details.png" alt="Détails du produit" loading="lazy" width="200" height="433" />
              <figcaption>Détails — Infos de compatibilité, prix, vendeur</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="screenshot">
              <img src="/axto-images/cart-empty.png" alt="Panier vide" loading="lazy" width="200" height="433" />
              <figcaption>Panier — État vide</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="screenshot">
              <img src="/axto-images/cart-with-products.png" alt="Panier avec articles" loading="lazy" width="200" height="433" />
              <figcaption>Panier — Articles prêts pour le paiement</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="screenshot">
              <img src="/axto-images/checkout-address.png" alt="Adresse de livraison" loading="lazy" width="200" height="433" />
              <figcaption>Paiement — Adresse de livraison</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="screenshot">
              <img src="/axto-images/checkout-credit-card.png" alt="Paiement par carte" loading="lazy" width="200" height="433" />
              <figcaption>Paiement — Carte bancaire via Stripe</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="screenshot">
              <img src="/axto-images/notifications.png" alt="Notifications" loading="lazy" width="200" height="433" />
              <figcaption>Notifications — Baisses de prix et messages</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="screenshot">
              <img src="/axto-images/profile.png" alt="Profil" loading="lazy" width="200" height="433" />
              <figcaption>Profil — Compte et recherches sauvegardées</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>

          <h2>Ce que j'ai appris</h2>
          <p>Mon premier marketplace full-stack et le projet où j'ai compris que <em>la gestion du périmètre est une compétence, pas une contrainte</em>. La liste de fonctionnalités n'arrêtait pas de s'allonger — avis, messagerie, notifications, analytics — et chacune m'a appris quelque chose sur la gestion d'état multiplateforme, la synchronisation temps réel, et pourquoi on ne saute pas les tests d'intégration de son webhook Stripe.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <nav class="project-nav">
      <div class="container project-nav-inner">
        <a href="/projects/mangaread" class="btn-ghost">← Projet précédent</a>
        <a href="/projects/yatsuscript" class="btn-ghost">Projet suivant →</a>
      </div>
    </nav>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
/* Hallmark · genre: modern-minimal · macrostructure: Long Document
 * design-system: design.md · designed-as-app
 */

/* ── Project Page Layout ── */
.project-page {
  padding-top: 7rem;
  padding-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
}

.project-cat {
  display: block;
}

.project-title {
  font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw + 0.5rem, var(--text-display));
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  line-height: 0.95;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
}

.project-tagline {
  font-size: var(--text-md);
  color: var(--color-muted);
  line-height: 1.65;
  max-width: 36rem;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  font-family: var(--font-body);
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .project-tagline { font-size: var(--text-lg); }
}

.project-links {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--space-sm);
  margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
}

.project-tech-stack {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--space-sm);
  padding-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
}

.tech-label {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: var(--text-xs);
  color: var(--color-muted);
  white-space: nowrap;
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
}

.tech-list {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: var(--space-2xs);
}

.project-content {
  max-width: 48rem;
}

.project-content h2 {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: var(--text-xl);
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
  margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
}

.project-content h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }

.project-content p {
  font-size: var(--text-base);
  color: var(--color-ink-2);
  line-height: 1.7;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
}

.project-content ul {
  list-style: disc;
  padding-left: var(--space-lg);
  margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
}

.project-content li {
  font-size: var(--text-base);
  color: var(--color-ink-2);
  line-height: 1.7;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-2xs);
}

.project-content li strong { color: var(--color-ink); }

.project-content code {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 0.85em;
  background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 8%, transparent);
  padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem;
  border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  color: var(--color-accent);
}

.project-content a {
  color: var(--color-accent);
  text-decoration: underline;
  text-underline-offset: 2px;
  text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
  text-decoration-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 40%, transparent);
  transition: all var(--dur-short) var(--ease-out);
}

.project-content a:hover {
  text-decoration-color: var(--color-accent);
}

.project-content a code {
  color: inherit;
  background: none;
  padding: 0;
}

.project-nav {
  padding: var(--space-xl) 0 var(--space-2xl);
}

.project-nav-inner {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
}

/* ── Screenshot Gallery ── */
.screenshot-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(160px, 1fr));
  gap: var(--space-md);
  margin: var(--space-lg) 0;
}

@media (min-width: 640px) {
  .screenshot-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(180px, 1fr));
  }
}

.screenshot {
  margin: 0;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
}

.screenshot img {
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
  background: var(--color-paper);
  box-shadow: 0 2px 8px color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-ink) 6%, transparent);
}

.screenshot figcaption {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: var(--text-xs);
  color: var(--color-muted);
  margin-top: var(--space-2xs);
  text-align: center;
  line-height: 1.4;
}
</style>
